  "texts": [
    "The last equality holds because p is a probability vector and thus s∈S p s = 1.",
    "We learn the judge by maximizing the probability of correct score predictions.",
    "This is equivalent to minimizing a regularized cross-entropy loss",
    ", where e t is the base judge's rationale, p t is a distribution over its scores, and s t is the human score in data point t ∈ [n].",
    "The regularization strength γ > 0 is set automatically by cross-validation."
